INSERT INTO `railway_infrastructure_collections` VALUES (1,'dowyvr5pfv8hr3ld8qjqw96q',' Shatin to Central Link Contract No. 1124 Admiralty SCL Related Works','Shatin to Central Link Contract No. 1124 Admiralty SCL Related Works','MTR Corporation Ltd.','18 March 2016 - 31 January 2022','<p>The major scope of this project consists of completing the Shatin Central Line (SCL) section of the new Admiralty Station. The new SCL part of the station is to be integrated with the existing station box as part of the environmental control system (ECS) relocation work. This requires sequential demolition and re-casting of some of the floor slabs. As the ECS works are to be carried out in phases, permanent escalators will need to be installed in the atrium space and the temporary public passageway across the atrium removed in phases.</p><br/><p>The works mainly comprise alteration and addition works at the interface between the existing Admiralty Station and the new Admiralty Station, including the design and construction of ABWF works and building service works, removal of existing public corridor, flying strut, escalator and its enclosure inside existing Admiralty Station.</p>','2025-06-01 08:57:24.936000','2025-07-07 07:22:23.349000',NULL,8,36,'en',1.00),(3,'bjlop2xqlyky77htj9gcgnxb','Contract K1434-14C Station Improvement Works at KOT','Contract K1434-14C Station Improvement Works at KOT','MTR Corporation Limited.','15 January 2015 - 16 June 2018','<p>This is a station improvement project located at one of the busiest stations – the Kowloon Tong Station, the interchange station of East Rail Line and Kwun Tong Line. All the works were carried out with minimal disruptions to the operating station. To achieve this, the project team implemented comprehensive logistic arrangement and detailed planning of work. We are proud that the works in the operating station were completed without causing any major nuisance and disturbance to the public.</p>','2025-06-01 09:05:10.190000','2025-07-07 07:22:24.756000',NULL,8,36,'en',2.00),(5,'hl9tkv72x2oc3i1nci3bt1xf','Wan Chai Station Lee Tung Street Subway (Contract C6593-13C)','Wan Chai Station Lee Tung Street Subway','MTR Corporation Limited','14 April 2014 - 18 July 2017','<p>The project involved constructing a 100m new pedestrian subway extending from the existing MTR Wan Chai Station concourse, running under Southorn Playground and across Johnston Road to the basement of the redeveloped Urban Renewal Authority (URA), and to modify the existing facilities. The pedestrian subway provided direct, convenient, safe and comfortable access for pedestrians and MTR passengers for crossing Johnston Road. It enhanced the connectivity of pedestrian facilities between north and south Wan Chai. Cut and cover method was used for the construction of pedestrian subway, while temporary traffic arrangements were arranged at Johnston Road during the construction period to maintain the daily ongoing traffic including trams and vehicles. In addition, the project also included the improvement works for the Southorn Stadium, including resurfacing the basketball mat and replacing facilities etc.</p>','2025-06-01 09:07:55.001000','2025-07-07 07:22:25.183000',NULL,8,36,'en',3.00),(7,'s4j5xho4f1rutlfrqwyrqyyu',' Shatin to Central Link Contract No. 1108 Kai Tak Station and Associated Tunnels','Shatin to Central Link Contract No. 1108 Kai Tak Station and Associated Tunnels','MTR Corporation Limited','25 April 2013 - 18 November 2018','<p>The Shatin to Central Link (SCL) is a government funded concessionary project providing a strategic rail corridor from Shatin to Central. One of the contracts of the Shatin to Central Link (SCL), the works comprise the construction of the Kai Tak Station and associate tunnels.</p><p>Consisting of 2 levels of RC box structure constructed by cut and cover method, this underground station is located in centre of Kai Tak Development Area. Upon completion of the project, Kai Tak residents will benefit as crossing the harbour will take much less time.</p>','2025-06-01 09:10:35.631000','2025-07-07 07:22:23.985000',NULL,8,36,'en',4.00),(9,'t62kciee9xeqj08fg5dc1bw2','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No. 1111 Hung Hom North Approach Tunnels','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No. 1111 Hung Hom North Approach Tunnels','MTR Corporation Limited','17 December 2012 - 18 November 2018','<p>The Shatin to Central Link (SCL) is a government funded concessionary project providing a strategic rail corridor from Shatin to Central. One of the contracts of the Shatin to Central Link (SCL). The scope of work is included Tunnels Works, Foundation Works, Site Formation Works, Bridge Works, Noise Enclosure Works and Demolition Works. This is a challenging project in terms of geographical location and work complexity, as this construction site will passes through the aged urban town Hung Hom where a huge amount of utilities are underground. Due to the location, extensive TTM arrangements and utilities diversion and/or protection has to be undertaken.</p>','2025-06-01 09:11:53.733000','2025-07-07 07:22:23.856000',NULL,8,36,'en',5.00),(11,'djk6lkzz29bby1z407kednbv','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No.1106 Diamond Hill Station','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No.1106 Diamond Hill Station','MTR Corporation Limited','17 December 2012 - 18 November 2018','<p>The 17-kilometre SCL was a territory-wide strategic railway project involving 10 stations, amongst which Diamond Hill was one of the six interchange stations. Upon the completion of Diamond Hill Station, it will become a new interchange station for the future SCL and the existing Kwun Tong Line.</p><p>The scope of SCL1106 included construction of a new SCL concourse and platforms and a wide array of enhanced facilities including the installation of 3 new lifts, 12 escalators, additional ticket issuing machines, automatic teller machines, shops, and new public toilet facilities. The scope also include the relocation of heritage structures and archaeological diggings.</p>','2025-06-01 09:15:02.969000','2025-07-07 07:22:23.876000',NULL,8,36,'en',6.00),(13,'fglanq2xxhlik5x37u6ji8uh','New Entrance and Concourse at University Station (Contract K0736-11C)','New Entrance and Concourse at University Station','MTR Corporation Limited','27 June 2011 - 29 July 2012','<p>Our group was awarded the improvement works of University Station, which mainly included the construction of a new station concourse with an area of 200m2 and entrance near the northern end of the uptrack platform, construction of a new covered walkway along uptrack platform, and design and build of an aluminium ceiling and monitor roof.</p>','2025-06-01 09:16:53.603000','2025-07-07 07:22:27.287000',NULL,8,36,'en',7.00),(15,'nyhg25nx0ubf2ephfvqtvvvl',' Admiralty Integrated Station and SCL Enabling Works (South Island Line (East) – Contract 901)','Admiralty Integrated Station and SCL Enabling Works','MTR Corporation Limited','18 May 2011 - 31 December 2016','<p>The South Island Line (East) is a medium-capacity railway connecting the MTR network at Admiralty to the Southern District of Hong Kong, via new stations at Ocean Park, Wong Chuk Hang, Lei Tung and South Horizons - a distance of approximately 7 km.</p><p>The primary objective of Contract 901 is to construct a new Admiralty Integrated Station in an urban centre with a very limited site area.  Under this contract, the existing Admiralty Station will be significantly extended to provide interchange facilities between the existing Tsuen Wan Line, the new South Island Line (East) and the proposed Shatin to Central Link. In addition to the four new platforms to be constructed below and adjacent to the existing station, the works include an interchange concourse, relocation of existing passenger entrances and external landscaping.</p><p>The Works under MTR Contract 901 comprise an extension east of the existing ADM station. The ADM integrated station will accommodate an interchange concourse, circulation areas and station cavern for SIL and SCL (Shatin Central Link). The extension is located under Harcourt Garden and is bounded by the existing ADM station, two existing finger platform box structures (Island Line and Tsuen Wan Line) and the existing underground Admiralty car park. The proposed platforms for SIL(E) and SCL will be constructed below and adjacent to the existing ADM.</p>','2025-06-01 09:18:15.093000','2025-07-07 07:22:25.575000',NULL,8,36,'en',8.00),(17,'hl90lvymsnvvhcynimq12vsd',' Ngau Tam Mei to Tai Kong Po Tunnels (Express Rail Link - Contract No. 824)','Ngau Tam Mei to Tai Kong Po Tunnels','MTR Corporation Limited','16 August 2010 - 31 May 2017','<p>XRL Contract 824 was one of the XRL tunnel contracts. The tunnel runs beneath the natural terrain of Lam Tsuen Country Park between Ngau Tam Mei in the north and Tai Kong Po in the south.  Drill-and-blast method was adopted for excavating the approximately 2.6 km tunnel. The rock nature is mainly volcanic tuff.</p><p>A temporary circular shaft was constructed at Tai Kong Po for mucking out and material delivery.  Two permanent shafts were subsequently constructed at both ends of the tunnels.  Most of the tunnel&#x27;s track was run on twin bore single track. These tunnels had an internal span of 7.8 m and an internal height of 7.6 m.  The project included the construction of a Crossover Cavern with an internal span of 22.2 m (resulting in an external span of circa 25 m), an internal height of 15.0 m and a length of 115 m. The cavern is 25 m away from the Ngau Tam Mei Shaft.  The existing design requires the construction of twin bore, single track running tunnels with overhead ventilation duct between the Ngau Tam Mei Shaft and the cavern to facilitate construction. This XRL Contract 824 also included the construction of a ventilation building at Ngau Tam Mei and an emergency access point at Tai Kong Po.</p><p>In line with the construction of the tunnels, there were also some external works associated with this contract which included widening of Chi Ho Road and Kong Tai Road, miscellaneous external works such as paving, landscaping, utilities works, earth works, ELS, piling / geotechnical works etc.</p>','2025-06-01 09:19:25.289000','2025-07-07 07:22:27.519000',NULL,8,36,'en',9.00),(19,'scwv2062fmp0yv3ctvwymy1a','Replacement of Ceiling Panels at Main Concourse of Hung Hom Station (Contract No. K8012-08C)','Replacement of Ceiling Panels at Main Concourse of Hung Hom Station','MTR Corporation Limited','13 November 2008 - 02 January 2009',NULL,'2025-06-01 09:20:46.341000','2025-07-07 07:22:26.694000',NULL,8,36,'en',10.00),(21,'qzbzpog538esdf6onduow9fh',' 沙田至中环綫: 合约编号1124 - 金钟站沙中綫相关工程','沙田至中环綫: 合约编号1124 - 金钟站沙中綫相关工程','香港铁路有限公司','2016 年 03 月 18 日 - 2022 年 01 月 31 日','<p>本项目的主要范围包括建造新金钟站的沙田中环线（沙中线）部分。环境控制系统（ECS）迁移工作的部分工作是需要将新沙中线部分车站与现有的车站整合。这需要依序拆除及重新建造部分楼板。由于环境控制系统工程将分阶段进行，因此需要在中庭空间安装永久扶手电梯，并分阶段拆除横跨中庭的临时公共通道。</p><p>此工程主要于现有金钟站和新金钟站进行改建及加建工程，包括设计及建造建筑及楼宇装修和屋宇设备工程，拆除现有公共走廊、吊杆、自动扶梯及其在现有金钟站内的围护结构。</p>','2025-06-01 09:22:07.976000','2025-07-07 07:22:11.815000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',1.00),(23,'ksv3yunvk56hpcrsgvk909jf',' 合约编号K1434-14C九龙塘站改善工程','合约编号K1434-14C九龙塘站改善工程','香港铁路有限公司','2015 年 01 月 15 日 - 2018 年 06 月 16 日','<p>这是香港铁路站内的改善工程项目. 项目位于香港其中一个最繁忙的铁路站-九龙塘站, 亦是东铁线与观塘线的中转站. 所有工程需在车站运行期间进行.为减低工程对车站的运作影响,完善的物流与工程计划是必要的.我们最终希望工程能够在对公众没任何影响下完成.</p>','2025-06-01 09:23:05.981000','2025-07-07 07:22:11.770000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',2.00),(25,'pfm38sp5ylwjofm9dy1w5bkb','湾仔站利东街行人隧道及出入口改善工程 (合约编号 C6593-13C)','湾仔站利东街行人隧道及出入口改善工程','香港铁路有限公司','2014 年 04 月 14 日 - 2017 年 07 月 18 日','<p>为提升车站设施及配合市区重建局的重建项目,并且改善湾仔南北行人设 施的连系,港铁公司决定进行湾仔站利东街行人隧道工程。 长约100米的利东街行人隧道途经修顿游乐场及庄士敦地道底,接驳港铁湾仔站大堂非付款区的西面及市区重建局于利东街的重建项目的商场地库。 隧道工程以明挖回填方法建造,工程期间,一段庄士敦道进行临时的交通安排,为确保道路行车及电车维持运作,现有电车轨道底需进行土力加固以便挖掘。 此外,工程还同时进行修顿运动场的优化工程,包括重铺篮球场地垫、更换休憩设施等。</p>','2025-06-01 09:24:21.864000','2025-07-07 07:22:11.814000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',3.00),(27,'aons8f78n2fpu4kxxob6kwrf',' 沙田至中环线 - 合约编号1108 启德站及相关隧道工程','沙田至中环线 - 合约编号1108 启德站及相关隧道工程','香港铁路有限公司','2013 年 04 月 25 日 - 2018 年 11 月 18 日','<p>沙中线为政府出资兴建的策略性铁路项目, 提供一条贯穿沙田与中环的走廊. 这是在众多沙中线合约的其中一份. 其合约要求兴建启德站及相关隧道, 这地下车站是由两层的混凝土结构组成. 车站位于启德发展区的中心. 当完工时, 启德市民出外的交通时间将会大大减低, 如过海时间将会大幅减低.</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-02 01:13:02.300000','2025-07-07 07:22:12.974000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',4.00),(29,'megckya2shsh8al8nel3nedr','沙田至中环线 - 合约编号1111 红磡站北面隧道工程','沙田至中环线 - 合约编号1111 红磡站北面隧道工程','香港铁路有限公司','2012 年 12 月 17 日 - 2018 年 11 月 18 日','<p>沙中线为政府出资兴建的策略性铁路项目, 提供一条贯穿沙田与中环的走廊. 这是在众多沙中线合约的其中一份. 其合约范围内的工程包括: 隧道工程, 基础工程, 地盘平整工程, 天桥工程, 防噪音设施工程与拆卸工程. 由于地盘的地理位置和工程的复习性, 这是一个富有挑战性的项目.在于地盘横跨了拥有大量地下公供设施路线的旧区红磡, 所以大型广泛的临时交通改道, 地下公供设施路线改道与保护也包含在这个顶目</p>','2025-06-02 01:15:00.220000','2025-07-07 07:22:11.830000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',5.00),(31,'b8dl7dywx40hz899tdufrdst','沙田至中环线 – 合约编号1106 钻石山站扩建工程','沙田至中环线 – 合约编号1106 钻石山站扩建工程','香港铁路有限公司','2012 年 12 月 17 日 - 2018 年 11 月 18 日','<p>沙中线全长 17 公里, 是一个全港策略性铁路项目，当中设有 10 个车站，钻石山站 是六个转线站中的其中一个。扩建后的钻石山站将会是未来沙中线及现时观塘线的转线站。</p><p>合约编号1106 钻石山站扩建工程除兴建新沙中线大堂及月台外车站亦会增加多项新设施，包括安装3 部新升降机和12 条新扶手电梯，增加自动售票机、自动柜员机和商铺，以及加设公众洗手间等。此外合约内容亦包括搬迁文物结构和考古发掘。</p>','2025-06-02 01:16:10.103000','2025-07-07 07:22:11.967000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',6.00),(33,'xkbu26y1qr9vf68qvoijvgh5','大学站新闸口及大堂工程 (合约编号 K0736-11C)','大学站新闸口及大堂工程','香港铁路有限公司','2011 年 06 月 27 日 - 2012 年 07 月 29 日','<p>集团于2011年获得一个改善港铁大学站的工程，主要工程包括在港铁大学车站北行线月台侧兴建一个面积约200平方米的入闸区大堂；沿港铁大学车站北行线兴建月台檐篷；设计及建造铝制天花及采光屋顶等。</p>','2025-06-02 01:17:09.084000','2025-07-07 07:22:11.980000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',7.00),(35,'wb2ruzzdgd1k5mzz6xbovhv9','金钟综合车站及沙中綫前期工程 (南港岛綫(东段) - 合约编号901)','金钟综合车站及沙中綫前期工程','香港铁路有限公司','2011 年 05 月 18 日 - 2016 年 12 月 31 日','<p>南港岛线主要连接香港岛中西区及南区,从金钟站出发,途经海洋公园、黄竹坑、利东及海怡半岛共五站,全长约7公里,车程需约10分钟,以中型铁路形式设计。</p><p>工程主要目标是在城市中心建造一个新的金钟综合车站,建造隧道连接到现有的金钟站。 工程完成后,现有的金钟站将会大大延伸,以提供现有荃湾线,南港岛线与沙田至中环线之间的换乘设施。 工程除了在现有车站毗邻下面建造四个新平台外,还包括交汇处,现有乘客出入口的搬迁和外部景观工程等。</p><p>地铁合约901工程包括延长现有金钟车站以东。 金钟车站可以将各线交汇,并提供中转区域及连接南港岛线和沙中线(沙田至中环线)。 延长部分的工程位于夏悫花园之下,并在现有的金钟车站、两个箱形结构的月台(港岛线及荃湾线)和现有的地下金钟停车场的范围内进行。 南港岛线(东段)和沙田至中环线月台则建造在现有金钟站之下的毗邻位