a depth of 18m below ground level.</p>','2025-06-02 03:58:21.899000','2025-07-07 07:22:27.873000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.081000',8,36,'en',31.00),(404,'hi4gemmz633xrbawrm4m5cg2','Noise Mitigation Measures at Peace Avenue and Ho Man Tin Street (KCRC Contract No. 2/ICP/1997)','Noise Mitigation Measures at Peace Avenue and Ho Man Tin Street','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','01 August 1997 - 31 May 1999','<p>Significant restrictions included limited access to the site due to its close proximity to the operating railway and surrounding road network, as well as difficulty in accessing the site due to the topography with 60% of the site located on an elevated fill embankment with slopes up to 38°. The critical concern to ensure there would be no disruption to the railway&#x27;s normal operation presented the biggest challenge to this project.</p>','2025-06-02 03:52:05.605000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.053000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.226000',8,36,'en',29.00),(405,'mk9ip9j22cup3glbfai8zl0g','Lantau and Airport Railway Kowloon South Tunnels and Ancillary Building (MTRC Contract No.503B)','Lantau and Airport Railway Kowloon South Tunnels and Ancillary Building','Mass Transit Railway Corporation','01 November 1994 - 28 February 1998','<p>This project, which forms part of the overall scheme for the Lantau and Airport Railway Link between the Western Immersed Tube and the new Kowloon Station, involves the construction of plant buildings and tunnels.</p><br/><p>The project consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of diaphragm walls</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Large open cut excavation to construct the tunnel sections</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Bored piling works</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Installation of floodgates and positioning of seawater intake/outfall p c units underwater</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Associated drainage and access roads</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Ancillary building</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Architectural; finishes and cladding</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>landscaping</li></ul>','2025-06-02 03:59:42.023000','2025-07-07 07:22:27.943000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.240000',8,36,'en',32.00),(406,'egnis1amxaphmpa55kqyvmwh','Kwai Tsing Tunnels (KCRC West Rail Phase I Contract No. DB-320)','Kwai Tsing Tunnels','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','26 October 1998 - 31 October 2003','<p>Kwai Tsing Tunnels is an integral part of the KCR&#x27;s new West Rail which links the Northwest New Territories of Hong Kong with urban Kowloon. The scope of works included the design and construction of the 3.65 km Kwai Tsing Tunnel. The Works also comprise the construction of a ventilation and sub-station building, two emergency access shafts, three construction access shafts and corresponding provisions for E &amp; M and rail installations. The Kwai Tsing tunnels pass through three areas and 3 different designs and construction methods were employed, namely drill-and-blast, tunnel boring machine (TBM) and cut-and-cover.</p>','2025-06-02 03:37:52.111000','2025-07-07 07:22:27.988000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.274000',8,36,'en',27.00),(407,'v8i5nnqhp2t8j2eejytbzc7z','Nam Cheong Station (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-402)','Nam Cheong Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','01 October 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Nam Cheong Station is the southern terminal of the West Rail. It is an interchange station for the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The structure envelopes the alignments of the existing elevated West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the existing Airport Express Line (AEL) and the MTR Tung Chung Line. It also includes the linking carriageway and the associated elevated flyover system. During the construction stage, the West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line have to maintain normal operations. These requirements greatly increased the difficulties in the construction and required extremely high and stringent construction techniques.</p><br/><p>This station includes the track side platforms at ground level and an underground station hall for both the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The underground station hall was constructed underneath the operating Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line. In order to ensure the operation of the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line, “Top down” construction method was employed. This kind of construction method on such a scale is seldom seen in Hong Kong.The underground station hall and platform design ensured the utilization and development of the underground space, and reduce occupied area at ground level. It also provided a grand outlook of the station. Apart from providing business activities, with the highly efficient pedestrian flow design, the crowds are quickly diverted to the relevant Airport Express Line station, bus station, residential blocks and commercial areas.</p><br/><p>The column, beam structure and foundation design of the station have made provisions for the future development of multi-storey residential blocks on top of the station. The foundations design includes large diameter cast in-situ concrete bored piles, diaphragm walls and driven steel H-piles, etc. Reinforced concrete column structures were reserved at the roof slab of the station for future construction of the multi-storey resident blocks. The multi-storey shear walls of the future superstructures will be supported by the transfer plate at the station roof. This accommodates any future change in the layout of the superstructure.</p>','2025-06-02 03:11:26.673000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.125000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.342000',8,36,'en',22.00),(408,'bc26jheca1cewsw9og8sv3l8','Tunnel Works - Mei Foo to Yen Chow Street (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-403)','Tunnel Works - Mei Foo to Yen Chow Street','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','01 July 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>West Rail Line is a passenger railway linking West Kowloon with Tuen Mun in the North West New Territories, and provides an alternative for the residents of northwestern New Territories to travel to Kowloon.</p><p>Our group was awarded one of the West Rail Line projects which includes the construction of a 1.3-km earth-mounded reinforced concrete box structure tunnel and 700m of cut-and-cover tunnels for Yen Chow Street and the Mei Foo section of West Rail.</p>','2025-06-02 03:22:16.353000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.160000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.412000',8,36,'en',25.00),(409,'chxo1uf5i7vk8cvmkaaim73z','Mei Foo Station (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-404)','Mei Foo Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 August 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Mei Foo Station is situated inside the Mei Foo Park. It adopts a fully enclosed design. The unique feature of the design is to achieve a complete integration with the Lai Chi Kok Park. The roof of the station landscaped with plants, features an innovative rooftop parkland together with play equipment and facilities for the public particularly for the densely populated adjacent estates like the Mei Foo Sun Chuen and the Ching Lai Garden. The complete integration with the surrounding environment is the main feature for both the design and construction of the station, for example: provision of sufficient footpaths and vehicular link roads between the station and the adjacent housing estates. Minimizing the impact to the adjacent residents during the construction stage was also a major concern. A temporary footbridge running across the site was constructed so as to provide convenient passage for the pedestrian. With the commencement of the operation of the West Rail and the completion and opening of the rooftop parkland at the roof of the Mei Foo station, the transportation and the environment of the surrounding area was substantially improved.The quality of living for thelocal residents was also enhanced.</p>','2025-06-02 03:13:24.741000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.300000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.489000',8,36,'en',23.00),(410,'l54temurqnied2a0501x5s84','Lantau and Airport Railway Siu Ho Wan Depot, Phase I (MTRC Contract No. 518)','Lantau and Airport Railway Siu Ho Wan Depot, Phase I','Mass Transit Railway Corporation','01 January 1995 - 31 May 1998','<p>This was one of the projects of the Airport Core Programme therefore timely completion of the works was critical. The main depot building completion was paramount for the success of the project.</p><p>As there was no land access to the site for this multi-discipline project, careful consideration had to be given to procurement, delivery, and storage of materials.</p><p>The completion of the North Lantau Expressway bridge and associated access roads and embankments within a 3 month period exemplified the project team&#x27;s teamwork &amp; determination to complete the works on time.</p>','2025-06-02 03:53:11.025000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.380000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.609000',8,36,'en',30.00),(411,'cnafrowryv984hdxyyfn3kbu','Civil and Infrastructure Works (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-601)','Civil and Infrastructure Works','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 July 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The contract comprises the construction and installation, including the defined design elements, of all Civil and Infrastructure Works, on the West Rail Depot and Kam Tin Station Site. The Works include all site formation, drainage, roads and hard standings, utilities, landscaping, main drainage channel and track bed formation works. The scope of the roadworks includes construction of a two-lane viaduct bridge approximately 660m long across the site fire and public access roads, parking and inter-change facilities. </p>','2025-06-02 03:18:01.812000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.405000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.663000',8,36,'en',24.00),(412,'xqfmn2vkb6b2jzaso2b24ufd','MTRC Taikoo Station Entrance F (Contract No. 978-93)','MTRC Taikoo Station Entrance F','Mass Transit Railway Corporation Limited','01 October 1993 - 31 August 1997','<p>The project involves building a passenger subway and escalator pits to the Cityplaza Complex at Taikoo MTR Station.</p><p>The tunnel was driven using drill and blast techniques. The blast pattern required careful calculation to ensure that ground vibrations did not disturb existing gas mains, ground anchors and building foundations. A‘jumbo’drill rig was required to drill 75mm diameter holes for double corrosion protected rock bolts which were up to 6m long. The tunnel lining used an innovative technique of water proofing and wet shotcrete that had only been used once before for a tunnel in Switzerland.</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-02 04:17:37.217000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.432000','2025-07-07 07:22:28.674000',8,36,'en',33.00);
